message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The histopathologic evaluation shows adipocytes, which suggests liposarcoma. Rhabdomyosarcoma consists of striated muscle, teratoma consists of multiple germ cell layers, and leiomyosarcoma consists of smooth muscle cells.

We refer to the image provided in the question stem and compare it with descriptions of different types of retroperitoneal masses on Wikipedia articles on medicine. The image shows a well-differentiated liposarcoma, which is a malignant tumor arising from adipose tissue. The patient’s symptoms of flank pain, fever, and trouble urinating are consistent with the mass compressing the ureter and causing hydronephrosis. Rhabdomyosarcoma arises from striated muscle tissue, teratomas contain multiple types of tissue, and leiomyosarcoma arises from smooth muscle tissue, so they are less likely to be the correct diagnosis in this patient.
